# NOTE: data/raw/1min.csv.gz and data/sample/ ARE committed on purpose — the
# raw CSV is the pipeline's input, not a build artifact.

# ...but an *unpacked* raw CSV must never be committed: it's ~105 MB, which
# exceeds GitHub's 100 MB per-file hard limit and would get the push rejected.
# Unpack it locally to inspect it:  npm run unpack
data/raw/*.csv
